dc_creator_sm: Snohomish County Geographic Information System (GIS), Dept. of Information Services
dc_description_s: This data set divides land areas based on the Public Land Survey System (PLSS). A quarter section is 1/4th of a Section, and is square shaped, roughly 1/2 mile on each side. Quarter Sections are typically identified by their position in the Section, for example NW 1/4 of Section 19.
dc_publisher_s: Snohomish County (WA) Geographic Information System (Snohomish GIS)
dc_title_s: Snohomish County, WA (Public Land Survey System Quarters, 2003)
